=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_FBSineC_ex6 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright gritty sound, with complex oscillator character around 53 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 53.2800
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.1484
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7475
  pitch_clarity: 20.5639
  inharmonicity: 0.0421
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -29.6536
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FBSineC Example 6
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/FBSineC.html
// Tags: FBSineC, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 6 ---
// randomly modulate params
(
{ FBSineC.ar(
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 1e4, 1e4),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 32, 33),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.5),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.05, 1.05),
    LFNoise2.kr(1, 0.3, 0.3)
) * 0.2 }.play(s);
)
